cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CL. 

The paper is about a benchmark for single object tracking, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning algorithms for tracking, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The evaluation of tracking algorithms involves statistical analysis, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The benchmark includes a large amount of video data, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of natural language for tracking, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
